Date: Mon 16 Jul 2018
Source: Reliefweb, a WHO report [edited]
https://reliefweb.int/report/yemen/yemen-cholera-response-weekly-epidemiological-bulletin-w26-2018-jun-25-jul-01-enar


Yemen: Cholera Response Weekly Epidemiological Bulletin: W26 2018 (Jun 25-Jul 01) [EN/AR]
----------------------------------------------------------------------

Cumulative figures
- The cumulative total from 27 Apr 2017 to 1 Jul 2018 is 1 115 378 suspected cholera cases and 2310 associated deaths, (case fatality rate [CFR] 0.21 per cent), 1157 have been confirmed by culture.
- The total proportion of severe cases among the suspected cases is 15.7 per cent
- The national attack rate is 397.4 per 10 000. The 5 governorates with the highest cumulative attack rates per 10 000 remain Amran (936), Al Mahwit (905), Al Dhale'e (641), Sana'a (550), Dhamar (540); -- children under 5 years old represent 28.8 per cent of total suspected cases.
- In total, 67 862 rapid diagnostic tests (RDT).
- 4459 cultures have been performed, which represents 26.2 per cent coverage.
- The last positive culture was on 29 Jun 2018 in Assafi'yah & Az'zal districts in Amanat Al Asimah.
- Since 1 Jan 2018 the districts with highest cumulative suspected cases are Al Hali (5841), Radman Al Awad (2215), Al Mighlaf (2150), Al Sabaeen (2102), Maqbanah (2075).
- 162 districts are still reporting suspected cholera cases in the past 3 weeks.
- 143 districts (out of 305 affected districts) have not reported any suspected cases for the past three consecutive weeks.

--
communicated by:
