Over the past 3 weeks of reporting, it appears that there have been 8234 additional cases. This new period is averaging about 392 cases PER DAY. The low case fatality rate might suggest that some of the diarrhea may be non-cholera. Although the daily rate has dropped significantly from the same period in 2017, this many new diarrhea cases per day remains substantial. There had been a slowing of cases during the 3-month period of January-March 2017 as well. The daily rate seems to be moving upwards a bit.

A map of Yemen: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5910388,126. - Mod.LL]
